    "fromName": "SourceNet Manager {managerName}",
    "subject": "Updated Network Access - Backup Server",
    "body": "Good, you accepted the restoration mission.\n\nI've negotiated with the client and secured NEW network credentials for you. After that disaster, they completely revoked your previous access, so this is a fresh NAR entry with different network permissions.\n\nThey've restructured their network access - you'll now connect to a different subnet with access to their backup-server. Click the attachment to add the new credentials to your Network Address Register.\n\nOnce you've added the credentials, use Network Scanner to find BOTH file systems: fileserver-01 (now empty after the sabotage) and backup-server (which has the backup copies).\n\nThen:\n1. Open TWO File Manager windows - one for each file system\n2. Copy all 8 log files from backup-server TO fileserver-01\n\nSimple copy job. Don't mess this up.\n\n- {managerName}"
  },
